    "description": "Hand-curated dense waypoint chains for narrow waterways. searoute's AIS-derived network is too sparse in channels like the Bosphorus / Dardanelles / Greek archipelago — a straight edge between two sparse nodes cuts across islands or peninsulas. Each chain is a sequence of (lat, lon) waypoints along the real navigable centerline. Consecutive waypoints are connected with direct edges (no land check — a maritime expert already vetted the path). Endpoints + intermediate nodes are wired into the broader graph via nearest-k search so any route crossing the region is forced through the chain.",
